  "notes": "Romanesco (Roman dialect). Central Italian of Rome and Lazio. Historically distinct from Tuscan, but re-Tuscanised from the 15th century onward due to the Papal court. Key features: (1) NO gorgia. (2) Rhotacism: /l/ → [r] before consonants (alto → [ˈarto]). (3) -ND- → [nː], -MB- → [mː]. (4) Affricate strengthening: /dʒ/ → [dːʒ] intervocalically. Literary tradition from Belli (19th c.) (D'Achille & Giovanardi 2001).",
